    "what_description": "Peumus boldus is a deciduous shrub or small tree native to the Andes mountains of South America, specifically in Chile and Argentina. It belongs to the family Myricaceae and is a member of the genus Peumus. The plant grows up to 5 meters in height, with a broad, rounded crown and a straight, columnar trunk. Its leaves are simple, alternate, and elliptical to obovate, measuring 8-15 centimeters in length, with a dark green color on the upper surface and a pale greenish-yellow color on the lower surface. The leaves have a leathery texture and a slightly wavy margin, with 10-20 pairs of secondary veins.",
