    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Peumus boldus are its antioxidant, antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, hepatoprotective, and antispasmodic activities. The plant's hepatoprotective properties are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which have been shown to reduce liver damage and inflammation. Antioxidant activity is also present, particularly due to the volatile oils and phenolic compounds that neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The plant's antimicrobial properties are responsible for its ability to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. The antispasmodic and anti-inflammatory activities of Peumus boldus are mediated by the glycosides and coumarins present in the plant, which help to relax smooth muscles and reduce inflammation.",
