    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Peumus boldus are boldine, quercetin, kaempferol, isoboldine, and isorhapontigenin. Boldine, a major alkaloid, exhibits antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and hepatoprotective properties, effectively reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the liver. Quercetin and kaempferol, two flavonoids, possess potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, scavenging free radicals and inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory mediators. Isoboldine, a minor alkaloid, has been shown to possess antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties, while isorhapontigenin, a lignan, demonstrates antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, potentially contributing to its anti-aging and anti-inflammatory effects. The collective actions of these constituents underlie the herb's therapeutic benefits, particularly in the management of liver disorders, inflammation, and oxidative stress.",
