    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Peumus boldus improperly include experiencing vomiting, which can lead to dehydration and electrolyte imbalance, as well as producing diarrhea, which can cause dehydration and weight loss. Inducing nausea can lead to loss of appetite and weight loss, as well as causing stomach discomfort and pain. Experiencing nausea can result in reduced food intake and poor nutrition, particularly in individuals with pre-existing gastrointestinal conditions. These side effects can be attributed to the plant's high levels of boldine, a toxic alkaloid that can cause gastrointestinal disturbances when consumed in excess. Improper use of Peumus boldus can also lead to allergic reactions, such as skin irritation and respiratory problems, in rare cases."
